# Pre-push CI checks

Before `git push` or `gh pr create`, run the same checks CI enforces (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`, invoked by `test.yml` on PRs and `deploy.yml` on `main`). Do not push if any step fails — fix first, then push.

## Backend (unit-test job)

From repo root:

```bash
uv run ruff check .
uv run ruff format --check .
uv run mypy .
uv run pytest -m "not retrieval and not generation"
```

Apply fixes when lint/format fail:

```bash
uv run ruff check --fix .
uv run ruff format .
```

## Frontend (frontend-test job)

When `frontend/` changed:

```bash
cd frontend && npm run lint && npm test
```

## Optional: pre-commit (commit time)

Pre-commit is configured in `.pre-commit-config.yaml` but opt-in (`uv run pre-commit install`). It runs Ruff + oxlint on commit — **not** mypy or pytest. Pre-push checks above still required.

## Test pitfalls

- CI unit-test has **no** `GEMINI_API_KEY`. `/chat` tests that hit `get_llm_settings()` must mock it (see `tests/db/test_generation.py` golden/poisoned cases).
- Retrieval/generation eval tests run in the separate `retrieval-test` job (needs Qdrant): `uv run pytest -m "retrieval or generation"`.
